ke Sontham'' (1989)\n# ''Kondaveeti Rowdy '' (1990)\n# ''[[Kodama Simham]]'' (1990) as Bar servant\n# ''[[Dagudumuthala Dampathyam]]'' (1990) as Rekha\n# ''Mama Alludu'' (1990) as Jaya\n# ''Maa Inti Katha'' (1990)\n# ''Doctor Bhavani'' (1990)\n# ''Chinna Kodalu'' (1991)\n# ''Rowdyism Nashinchali'' (1990)\n# ''Prema Yuddham'' (1990)\n# ''Irugillu Porugillu'' (1991)\n# ''Parishkaram'' (1991) as Jyothi\n# ''Sarpayagam'' (1991)\n# ''Nenera Police'' (1991)\n# ''Collector Gaari Alludu'' (1992)\n# ''[[Gharana Mogudu]]'' (1992) as Bhavani\n# ''[[Seetapathi Chalo Tirupathi]]'' (1992) as Aliveelu Mangatayaru\n# ''Palleturi Pellam'' (1992)\n# ''Alexander'' (1992)\n# ''[[Samrat Ashoka]]'' (1992) as Tishya Raksha\n# ''Vadinagaari Gajulu'' (1992)\n# ''Joker'' (1993) as Usha Rani\n# ''Ladies Special'' (1993) as Hema\n# ''Mama Kodalu'' (1993)\n# ''Prema Chitram Pelli Vichitram'' (1993)\n# ''[[Gangmaster (film)|Gangmaster]]'' (1994) as Swapna\n# ''Raitu Bharatam'' (1994)\n# ''Prema & Co.'' (1994)\n# ''Presidentugari Alludu'' (1994)\n# ''[[God Father (1995 film)|God Father]]'' (1995) as Rani\n# ''Adavilo Arunakka'' (1998)\n# ''Action No. 1'' (2002) as Kiron\n# ''Mudhu'' (2006)\n# ''[[Jaya Janaki Nayaka]]'' (2017) as Aswith Narayana's sister\n{{colend}}\n\n===Tamil===\n# ''[[Mannukkul Vairam]]'' (1986) Debut film\n# ''[[Nallavan (1988 film)|Nallavan]]'' (1988)\n# ''[[Poonthotta Kaavalkaaran|Poonthotta Kaavalkaran]]'' (1988)\n# ''[[Thaimel Aanai]]'' (1988)\n# ''[[Ithu Engal Neethi]]'' (1988)\n# ''Sanghu Pushpangal'' (1989)\n# ''[[My India]]'' (1997)\n# ''Jaya'' (2002)\n# ''[[Idhaya Thirudan]]'' (2005) as Sudharani\n\n===Kannada===\n# ''[[Mangalya (film)|Mangalya]]''    (Kannada) (1991)\n# ''Bombay Dada'' (1991) \n# ''[[Ranabheri]]''   (Kannada) (1990)\n# ''[[Parashuram (film)|Parashuram]]'' (1989) .... Usha\n\n===Hindi===\n# ''[[Bhishma (1996 film)|Bhishma]]'' (1996) (Vani Vishwanath as Paro) .... With Superstar [[Mithun Chakraborty]]\n# ''[[Jung (1996 film)|Jung]]'' (1996) (Vani Vishwanath) .... With Superstar [[Mithun Chakraborty]]\n\n==Television==\n*''Mattoruval'' (2010)....Annie (Surya TV)\n*''Kaatrinile Varum Geetham'' (SUN TV) .... Gayathri Devi\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{rotten tomatoes}}\n* [http://en.msidb.org/displayProfile.php?category=actors&artist=Vani%20Viswanath&limit=43 Vani Viswanath at MSI]\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Viswanath, Vani}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Kerala State Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Thrissur]]\n[[Category:St. Raphael's Convent Girls High School alumni]]\n[[Category:Telugu Desam Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Malayali politicians]]\n[[Category:Indian actor-politicians]]\n[[Category:Women in Andhra Pradesh politics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vani Viswanath\n| image              = \n| image_upright      = \n| native_name        = \u0d35\u0d3e\u0d23\u0d3f \u0d35\u0d3f\u0d36\u0d4d\u0d35\u0d28\u0d3e\u0d25\u0d4d\n| native_name_lang   = ml\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1971|5|13}}\n| birth_place        = [[Ollur]], [[Thrissur]], [[Kerala]], India\n| nationality        = Indian\n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Actress\n| years_active       = 1989\u2013present\n| party              = [[Telugu Desam Party]]\n| spouse             = {{marriage |[[Baburaj (actor)|Baburaj]]|2002}}\n| mother             = Girija\n| father             = Thazhathuveettil Vishwanathan\n| children           = {{ubl|Aarcha, Adhri}}\n| awards             = {{Awd|[[Kerala State Film Awards]]|2000}}\n}}\n'''Vani Viswanath''' (born 13 May 1971) is an [[Indian film]] actress. She joined in [[Telugu Desam Party]] in [[Andhra Pradesh]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/mb4eves/online/malayalam/kerala/women/articles/infocus_interview-article-210230 |title=In Focus interview - Vani Viswanath |work=Mathrubhumi |access-date=11 December 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131127015107/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/mb4eves/online/malayalam/kerala/women/articles/infocus_interview-article-210230 |archive-date=27 November 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 2000, Vani won the [[Kerala State Film Award for Second Best Actress]] for her performance in ''[[Susanna (2000 film)|Susanna]]'', directed by [[T. V. Chandran]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.screenindia.com/old/20010316/renews.htm|title=Kerala State Film Awards - 2000|date=16 March 2001|publisher=[[Screen (magazine)|Screen]]|accessdate=3 December 2009}}</ref> She was termed as [[Mollywood movie|Mollywood]]'s \"Action Queen\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article304239.ece |title=With guns blazing|publisher=The Hindu|accessdate=2011-11-04}}</ref>  In 1986, she made her acticg debut through th e Mannukkul Vairam (1986) \n\n==Early life==\nVani was born as the fourth among the five children of [[Malayali]] parents Thazhathuveettil Vishwanathan, an astrologer and Girija, a housewife in [[Ollur]], [[Thrissur]] in 1971. When she was 13, her father predicted through astrology that she will become an actor and also she will enter into the politics.<ref>http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/210231/</ref> Her mother hails from Ernakulam District and her father hails from Thrissur District.<ref>http://www.nostalgiamag.in/details.php?cat=&id=451</ref> She has four siblings.\n\nShe studied at [[Thrissur]] till fourth grade, later the family shifted to [[Madras]] and continued her education there till tenth grade. She got her first role while she was studying in tenth grade and hence she discontinued her studies and concentrated on her movie career.<ref>http://cinidiary.com/people.php?pigsection=Actor&picata=2&no_of_displayed_rows=40&no_of_rows_page=10&sletter=</ref>\n\n==Career==\nShe has appeared predominantly in [[Malayalam]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] movies. She acted in ''[[The King (1995 film)|The King]]'' with [[Mammootty]]. She also appeared in Kannada and Tamil movies. She was among the big stars of her time in the [[South India]]. Her [[Telugu cinema|Tollywood]] movie ''[[Gharana Mogudu]]'' with Tollywood superstar, [[Chiranjeevi]] was a huge hit. Vani is trained in fighting and martial arts and has fought even several men bravely in the films. Vani also acted in two Hindi film with Superstar [[Mithun Chakraborty]] in ''[[Jung (1996 film)|Jung]]'' and ''[[Bhishma (1996 film)|Bhishma]]''.\n\n==Horse Riding Profession==\nVani was a professional horse rider before entering film. She won several horse riding competitions. At one time, she was considered to be India's No. 1 Women's jockey. She is also a famous Bullet motorcycle rider, who participated in several bullet races. She also has a [[Black belt (martial arts)|black belt]] in [[Karate]].\n\n==Personal life==\nWhile acting for several films with [[Baburaj (actor)|Baburaj]], she fell in love with him. The couple got married in 2002 and have two children, Aarcha (born in 2002) and Adhri (born in 2008).<ref>{{cite web|title=\u0d07\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d1f\u0d46 \u0d0e\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\u0d3e\u0d35\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d38\u0d41\u0d16\u0d02 \u0d24\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d46..!|url=http://www.mangalam.com/women/personality/356025?page=0,4|publisher=mangalam.com|accessdate=4 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n;[[Kerala State Film Awards]]\n* 2000 - [[Kerala State Film Award for Second Best Actress|Second Best Actress]] - ''[[Susanna (2000 film)|Susanna]]''\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Malayalam===\n{{colbegin|colwidth=22em}}\