a\n* ''[[Vendicata!]]'' (1956)\n* ''[[War and Peace (1956 film)|War and Peace]]'' (1956) - Lisa Bolkonskaya\n* ''Un giglio infranto'' (1956) - Contessa Amelia Renzi\n* ''Porta un bacione a Firenze'' (1956) - Simonetta\n* ''Occhi senza luce'' (1956) - Daisy Ellis\n* ''[[The Black Devil (film)|The Black Devil]]'' (1957) - Isabella\n* ''[[The Flesh Is Weak]]'' (1957) - Marissa Cooper\n* ''La canzone del destino'' (1957) - Elena\n* ''[[Battle of the V-1]]'' (1958) - Anna\n* ''[[Ten Ready Rifles]]'' (1959) - Luc\u00eda\n* ''Checkerboard'' (1959) - Prostitute\n* ''[[Hannibal (1959 film)|Hannibal]]'' (1959) - Danila\n* ''[[A Breath of Scandal]]'' (1960) - Can-Can girl\n* ''[[Revak the Rebel]]'' (1960) - Princess Cherata\n* ''[[Days of Fire]]'' (1968) - Anna\n* ''[[Be Sick... It's Free]]'' (1968)\n* ''[[Let's Have a Riot]]'' (1970)\n* ''La grande avventura di Scaramouche'' (1972) - The Queen of France (final film role)\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0899890}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vitale, Milly}}\n[[Category:1933 births]]\n[[Category:2006 deaths]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Rome]]\n[[Category:Italian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Italian people of Russian descent]]\n[[Category:20th-century Italian actresses]]\n[[Category:Disease-related deaths in Italy]]\n\n\n{{Italy-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image       = Milly Vitale.jpg \n| name        = Milly Vitale\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|1933|7|16|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Rome, Italy]]\n| birth_name  = Camilla Vitale\n| death_date  = {{Death date and age|2006|11|2|1933|7|16|df=yes}}\n| death_place = Rome, Italy\n| occupation  = Actress\n| yearsactive = 1947\u20131972\n| spouse      = Vincent Hillyer\t(1960\u20131966)\n| children    = Edoardo Hillyer (b. 1961)<br/>Vincent Hillyer Jr. (b. 1964)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.glamourgirlsofthesilverscreen.com/show/401/Milly+Vitale/index.html |title=Milly Vitale Profile |website=Glamour Girls of the Silver Screen |access-date=2 April 2018}}</ref>\n| parents     = Riccardo Vitale<br/>Natasha Shidlowski\n}}\n\n'''Camilla \"Milly\" Vitale''' (16 July 1933 \u2013 2 November 2006) was an Italian actress. She was the daughter of Riccardo Vitale (Rome Opera House Director, deceased 1979)  and choreographer Natasha Shidlowski Vitale (deceased 1994).\n\nShe appeared in numerous post-war Italian films. She appeared in a few [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] movies but never achieved star status like her contemporaries [[Sophia Loren]] and [[Gina Lollobrigida]]. In her most notable U.S. role, she appeared with [[Bob Hope]] as \"Madeleine Morundo Foy\" in ''[[The Seven Little Foys]]'' (1956). She was featured in ''[[The Juggler (film)|The Juggler]]'' co-starring with [[Kirk Douglas]] (1953) and in the epic film ''[[War and Peace (1956 film)|War and Peace]]'' (1956).\n\n==Personal life==\nShe married Vincent Hillyer, a United States citizen, in 1960; the marriage produced two sons, Edoardo and Vincent Jr. The couple divorced about 1970. Vitale retired from acting in the early 1970s, after a career of more than 47 films. She died in Rome in 2006.\n\n==Selected filmography==\n{{div col|content=\n* ''[[The Brothers Karamazov (1947 film)|The Brothers Karamazov]]'' (1947) - Lisa\n* ''[[Difficult Years]]'' (1948) - Maria\n* ''[[Buried Alive (1949 film)|Buried Alive]]'' (1949) - Eva\n* ''La citt\u00e0 dolente'' (1949) - Maria\n* ''[[Black Magic (1949 film)|Black Magic]]'' (1949) - (uncredited)\n* ''La figlia del peccato'' (1949) - Lucia\n* ''[[The Lion of Amalfi]]'' (1950) - Eleonora\n* ''[[The Fighting Men]]'' (1950) - Elena Occhipinti\n* ''[[Hearts at Sea]]'' (1950) - Fioretta\n* ''[[Il Caimano del Piave]]'' (1951) - Lucilla di Torrebruna\n* ''[[Revenge of the Pirates]]'' (1951) - Luana\n* ''[[Cameriera bella presenza offresi...]]'' (1951) - Nandina, l'amante di Leonardi\n* ''[[Trieste mia!]]'' (1